I have been to Roti a bunch of times for lunch and love the food. However, I had a different experience when making a large order for a corporate event. I made the order for delivery online for 11 people. One of the orders was incorrect - someone ordered salmon since she cannot eat meat, but her order came with chicken. Not a big deal, mistakes happen.  When I called the restaurant to request they send over the correct order, the person I spoke with was very rude and told me they used chicken since they were out of salmon, and to get in touch with the delivery person (through DoorDash) and have them go back and pick it up, then promptly hung up on me.  I'm not sure how it becomes my responsibility to contact a courier to correct an order that the restaurant got wrong, and I am also surprised that I was not contacted about them being out of salmon. That, combined with the rudeness on the phone, will cause me to think twice about ordering for another corporate event.

Roti Mediterranean was delicious, colorful and flavorful. When you walk in, the restaurant is spacious and all of the ingredients are displayed at the counter. I loved the assortment of toppings and dressings you can add to make the bowl yours. I would give 5 stars if the restaurant was cleaner. But overall the food was good and flavorful.
